<td valign="top">

<center><table width="96%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><col width="64"><col width="15"><tr><td bgcolor="f0f0f0f" background="25pxheading.gif" align="center" height="25"><font face="arial" color="000000" size="3"><b>The Fear of All Sums </b></font></td></tr><tr><td align="center"> <font size="2" face="arial">Posted By <a href="mailto:gremmi@data-zoid.com">Gremmi</a> on Thursday 31st July, 2003 @ 19:50 (Read: 501) &nbsp;<a href="printnews.php?id=74"><img src="http://www.data-zoid.com/brutallyhonest/images/print.gif" border="0" Alt="Printable Version"></a></font></td></tr><tr><td width="93%" valign="top"><div><br><font size="2" face="arial">
<a href="searchcat.php?cid=11">
<img src="http://www.data-zoid.com/brutallyhonest/images/category/bhmr.gif" border="0" align="right" hspace="10" vspace="10" alt="Brutally Shite">
</a>

<img src="http://ia.imdb.com/media/imdb/01/I/21/46/02m.jpg" align="left"> 

<table width="250">
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#F8F3D7">
<font size="2" face="arial">IMDB: <a href="" target="new"></a><br>
Buy this here: <a href="" target="new">Buy!</a><BR></font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>

<br>
<font size="2" face="arial"> Or The Sum of All Fears. Whatever. Either way it's a great movie warning about the dangers of the Cold War superpowers facing off against each other. Wait..<br><br>Didn't that crap end a decade ago? Oh well, it's Tom Clancy, and if there is anyone here who can make you believe the world's going down the drain, it's him.<br />
<br />
This movie plays off the old cold war paranoia of the Americans and Russians being duped into blowing each other to smitherines with an assload of Nuclear weapons. Of course, the fact that it's supposed to take place in modern times may cause a double take. Even more ridiculous, it's set in motion by a vast right wing conspiracy! That includes Nazis! Wow, I guess Clinton was right.<br />
<br />
It's essentially a movie that establishes how the man with two first names, Jack Ryan, is always right, and thus can save the world at the last possible second. It's a relatively tired climax to have disaster averted at the last minute, but at least when that disaster is the end of the world, you have a little maneuvering room to have other disasters actually happen. One of these being a nice big explosion.<br />
<br />
This movie handles how we would respond to certain disasters a little bit inaccurately, but is otherwise believable enugh to enjoy, because these innacuracies are mostly just ones showing how reckless the main character can be. Also, they reduce the impact of a nuclear disaster and show us to be at a readiness level that we nowhere near approach in real life.<br />
<br />
But since we're talking about a Nazi plot to trick America and Russia into killing each other here, willful suspension of disbelief is required.<br />
<br />
Screwups aside, the movie tells an interesting enough story. Morgan Freeman's acting is pretty damn good, and ol' Ben doesn't do such a bad job either.<br />
<br />
Really, I only have one issue that bugs me, that's so unrealistic, and done so incorrectly, that I just HAVE to be irritated with this film.<br />
<br />
The climax comes down to Jack Ryan pretty much IMing the leader of Russia trying to warn them of the evil plot and get them to not vape everything in site. This is all well and good, but it's so unbelievable because he makes a well articulated speech via IM.<br />
<br />
Anyone who knows how it is in the real world know it'd be rather different. So here I present to you: If the movie took place in the real world -- the climax.<br />
<br />
<b>CIA_Dude69</b> would be Jack Ryan's screen name.<br />
<b>Soviet_Badass</b> would be the name of the Russian president.<br />
<br />
CIA_Dude69: dood, teh bombs r teh suxxor <img src="http://www.data-zoid.com/brutallyhonest/images/smile/sad.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
Soviet_Badass: wtf?<br />
CIA_Dude69: the nazis!!!!!!!!!!!11111<br />
Soviet_Badass: u sux, leave me alone<br />
CIA_Dude69: but tehnazis r 3vil! they goining to laff @ u for bein dum<br />
Soviet_Badass: ...<br />
CIA_Dude69: don't blow up teh wor..<br />
CIA_Dude69 has disconnected... (Connection Reset by a peer)<br />
<br />
Soviet_Badass: haha! lamer. by americnan pigdog! <br />
<br />
*world ends*<br />
<br />
</font></div>
